.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
This directory contains the source code for the Bitcoin Core graphical user interface (GUI)\&. It uses the [Qt](https://www1.qt.io/developers/) cross-platform framework\&.

.PP
The current precise version for Qt is specified in \fRqt_details\&.mk\fP\&.
.SS "Compile and run"
See build instructions: \fBUnix\fP, \fBmacOS\fP, \fBWindows\fP, \fBFreeBSD\fP, \fBNetBSD\fP, \fBOpenBSD\fP

.PP
When following your systems build instructions, make sure to install the \fRQt\fP dependencies\&.

.PP
To run:

.PP
.PP
.nf
\&./build/bin/bitcoin\-qt
.fi
.PP
.SS "Files and Directories"
.SS "forms/"
.IP "\(bu" 2
A directory that contains \fRDesigner UI\fP files\&. These files specify the characteristics of form elements in XML\&. Qt UI files can be edited with \fBQt Creator\fP or using any text editor\&.
.PP
.SS "locale/"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Contains translations\&. They are periodically updated and an effort is made to support as many languages as possible\&. The process of contributing translations is described in \fBdoc/translation_process\&.md\fP\&.
.PP
.SS "res/"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Contains graphical resources used to enhance the UI experience\&.
.PP
.SS "test/"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Functional tests used to ensure proper functionality of the GUI\&. Significant changes to the GUI code normally require new or updated tests\&.
.PP
.SS "bitcoingui\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Represents the main window of the Bitcoin UI\&.
.PP
.SS "*model\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
The model\&. When it has a corresponding controller, it generally inherits from \fRQAbstractTableModel\fP\&. Models that are used by controllers as helpers inherit from other Qt classes like \fRQValidator\fP\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBClientModel\fP is used by the main application \fRbitcoingui\fP and several models like \fRpeertablemodel\fP\&.
.PP
.SS "*page\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
A controller\&. \fR:NAMEpage\&.cpp\fP generally includes \fR:NAMEmodel\&.h\fP and \fRforms/:NAME\&.page\&.ui\fP with a similar \fR:NAME\fP\&.
.PP
.SS "*dialog\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Various dialogs, e\&.g\&. to open a URL\&. Inherit from \fRQDialog\fP\&.
.PP
.SS "paymentserver\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
(Deprecated) Used to process BIP21 payment URI requests\&. Also handles URI-based application switching (e\&.g\&. when following a bitcoin:\&.\&.\&. link from a browser)\&.
.PP
.SS "walletview\&.(h/cpp)"
.IP "\(bu" 2
Represents the view to a single wallet\&.
.PP
.SS "Other \&.h/cpp files"
.IP "\(bu" 2
UI elements like \fBBitcoinAmountField\fP, which inherit from QWidget\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fR\fBbitcoinstrings\&.cpp\fP\fP: automatically generated
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fRbitcoinunits\&.(h/cpp)\fP: BTC / mBTC / etc\&. handling
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fRcallback\&.h\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fR\fBguiconstants\&.h\fP\fP: UI colors, app name, etc\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fR\fBguiutil\&.h\fP\fP: several helper functions
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fRmacdockiconhandler\&.(h/mm)\fP: macOS dock icon handler
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fRmacnotificationhandler\&.(h/mm)\fP: display notifications in macOS
.PP
.SS "Contribute"
See \fBCONTRIBUTING\&.md\fP for general guidelines\&.

.PP
\fBNote:\fP Do not change \fRlocal/bitcoin_en\&.ts\fP\&. It is updated \fRautomatically\fP\&.
.SS "Using Qt Creator as an IDE"
\fRQt Creator\fP is a powerful tool which packages a UI designer tool (Qt Designer) and a C++ IDE into one application\&. This is especially useful if you want to change the UI layout\&.
.SS "Download Qt Creator"
On Unix and macOS, Qt Creator can be installed through your package manager\&. Alternatively, you can download a binary from the \fRQt Website\fP\&.

.PP
\fBNote:\fP If installing from a binary grabbed from the Qt Website: During the installation process, uncheck everything except for \fRQt Creator\fP\&.
.SS "macOS"
.PP
.nf
brew install qt\-creator
.fi
.PP
.SS "Ubuntu & Debian"
.PP
.nf
sudo apt\-get install qtcreator
.fi
.PP
.SS "Setup Qt Creator"
.IP "1." 4
Make sure you've installed all dependencies specified in your systems build instructions
.IP "2." 4
Follow the compile instructions for your system, adding the \fR-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug\fP build flag
.IP "3." 4
Start Qt Creator\&. At the start page, do: \fRNew\fP -> \fRImport Project\fP -> \fRImport Existing Project\fP
.IP "4." 4
Enter \fRbitcoin-qt\fP as the Project Name and enter the absolute path to \fRsrc/qt\fP as Location
.IP "5." 4
Check over the file selection, you may need to select the \fRforms\fP directory (necessary if you intend to edit *\&.ui files)
.IP "6." 4
Confirm the \fRSummary\fP page
.IP "7." 4
In the \fRProjects\fP tab, select \fRManage Kits\&.\&.\&.\fP

.PP
\fBmacOS\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRKits\fP: select the default "Desktop" kit
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRCompilers\fP: select \fR"Clang (x86 64bit in /usr/bin)"\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRDebuggers\fP: select \fR"LLDB"\fP as debugger (you might need to set the path to your LLDB installation)
.PP

.PP
\fBUbuntu & Debian\fP

.PP
Note: Some of these options may already be set
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRKits\fP: select the default "Desktop" kit
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRCompilers\fP: select \fR"GCC (x86 64bit in /usr/bin)"\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Under \fRDebuggers\fP: select \fR"GDB"\fP as debugger
.PP

.IP "8." 4
While in the \fRProjects\fP tab, ensure that you have the \fRbitcoin-qt\fP executable specified under \fRRun\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
If the executable is not specified: click \fR"Choose\&.\&.\&."\fP, navigate to \fRbuild/bin\fP, and select \fRbitcoin-qt\fP
.PP

.IP "9." 4
You're all set! Start developing, building, and debugging the Bitcoin Core GUI 
.PP

